    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="590"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/985</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_VDH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Van Dyke</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-27">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5:45 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>54. Your 47, 24th. Foreign Minister says meat products not among prohibited
                    exports because meat is plenty in Netherlands. Embargo intended to cover only
                    things specially needed in this country. Articles added to prohibited exports
                    since my 45 of October 12 are: potatoes, lead, cheese. This completes list to
                    date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VDH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Van Dyke</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
